  <li id="comment-16474" class="comment even thread-even depth-1">
    <header class="comment--meta">
      <div class="vcard"><cite class="comment-author fn"><a href="https://www.blogger.com/profile/01968703151905016369" class="url" rel="ugc external nofollow">Di</a></cite></div>
      <a href="https://orangette.net/2010/05/you-deserve-a-waffle/#comment-16474"><time class="comment-time" datetime="2010-05-18T03:41:15-04:00">Tuesday, May 18, 2010 at 3:41 am</time></a>    </header>

    
    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>You might want to try the Cook&#39;s Illustrated recipe with your Belgian waffle maker&#8211;the batter is thicker, since it has less liquid.  I also like to add a bit of freshly grated nutmeg to the batter.  I don&#39;t think it would be hard to convert to use active dry yeast&#8211;I&#39;d use a full package of active dry (about 2 1/4 tsp), and mix the yeast with the milk/melted butter mixture once it&#39;s cool enough.</p>
    </div>

