    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>After your last post about waffles I realized I hadn&#39;t made waffles in forever.  And I didn&#39;t want to take the time to make my sourdough ones.  I ended up with Ricotta Waffles from Dories book but I wanted sweet instead of savory.  I made a double batch, added 1/4 cup sugar to make them slightly sweet and a 1/4-1/2 tsp Fiori Di Sicilia instead of black pepper.  I was hide the leftovers from my kids.  We ate them with La Lechera<br />Sweetened Condensed Milk instead of maple syrup.</p>
