    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>I&#39;m too busy making chili and cornbread right now and so I&#39;ll read the other comments later, but &#8212; did you try each type of waffle at room temp?  and, dare I say it, cold?  (Did you even have leftovers to do so?)  </p>
<p>I am one of those folks who would much rather eat my waffles and pancakes at room temperature&#8230; and plain.  At room temp, they taste like what they are, which is a quickbread.  (Also, I ate so many Aunt Jemima pancake syrup-soaked waffles and pancakes growing up that the thought of anything sweet on these breads sometimes makes me gag a little.  I will use a little jam, honey, or sorghum now and then.)</p>
<p>Anyhow, you had a terrific journey to good waffles.  Thanks for sharing it with us.</p>
