  <li id="comment-16625" class="comment odd alt thread-odd thread-alt depth-1">
    <header class="comment--meta">
      <div class="vcard"><cite class="comment-author fn">Anna</cite></div>
      <a href="https://orangette.net/2010/05/you-deserve-a-waffle/#comment-16625"><time class="comment-time" datetime="2011-02-22T01:54:26-05:00">Tuesday, February 22, 2011 at 1:54 am</time></a>    </header>

    
    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>I&#39;ve been making these for over a year now, and the only thing I will say is that to achieve the crispness you must have a very hot waffle iron  as you pour the batter in.  I lightly brush some oil onto the grill and close the lid and wait a  little, lift the lid and if it is &#39;smoking&#39;  it is ready.  And make sure you do not raise the lid too soon or the inside will be too creamy.  Touch the waffle &#8211;  if it is too soft, or too light in colour, put the lid back on to brown some more. We have a really old General Electric Waffle Iron with a Low Medium and High setting, and I always go between Medium and High. These are the ONLY waffles we will eat!</p>
    </div>

