    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>Okay, I know it doesn&#39;t sound possible, but the Waffle of Insane Greatness is even Insanely Greater with a cup of cream subbed for the milk/buttermilk. I just did it because it was the only dairy we had in the house, not because I am a glutton (although I am). But. BUT. They had this extra-shattery thing going on on the outside? And this buttery crumb all the way through? We could not get over it.</p>
<p>I added a TBSP of lemon juice to the cream to maintain the acidity, and subbed in 1/4 of spelt flour, too. The batter was a bit thicker than usual. Maybe not an everyday version, but good for holiday mornings!</p>
